1.title: Italian Night at Rooster's

episode of.title: Home for Dinner with Jamie Deen (TV Series 2012– )

1.plot: Jamie helps his son open a backyard Italian restaurant. The menu includes stuffed shells with spinach and ricotta; roasted garlic-and-herb bread; salad with sliced radish and grape tomato; and crispy rice-caramel treats.

2.title: Fired Up!

episode of.title: Home for Dinner with Jamie Deen (TV Series 2012– )

2.plot: Jamie cooks with volunteers at his local fire station. Dishes include grilled pizza two ways; bacon-wrapped shrimp; and grilled hearts of romaine.

3.title: Kiddie Camping

episode of.title: Home for Dinner with Jamie Deen (TV Series 2012– )

3.plot: A meal that's nutritious & delicious is prepared for a backyard campout. Included: homemade peanut-butter energy bars; roasted carrot-and-basil soup with grilled cheese dunkers; oven-roasted sweet-potato fries; & fresh strawberry Popsicles.

4.title: Dad Food

episode of.title: Home for Dinner with Jamie Deen (TV Series 2012– )

4.plot: Jamie prepares his favorite foods for Father's Day, including grilled flank steak; roasted balsamic red onions; broccoli and silvered Parmesan salad; and for dessert, a brownie sundae.

5.title: Taco Night Done Right!

episode of.title: Home for Dinner with Jamie Deen (TV Series 2012– )

5.plot: Jamie cooks Mexican food with a Southern twist. Included: turkey tacos; a cheesy rice casserole; grilled-corn salsa; seven-layer bars; and boiled peanuts.

6.title: Win or Lose, You Gotta Eat

episode of.title: Home for Dinner with Jamie Deen (TV Series 2012– )

6.plot: On the menu: smoked pork butt; Brunswick stew; vinegar coleslaw; and baked beans made from scratch.

7.title: Summer Party

episode of.title: Home for Dinner with Jamie Deen (TV Series 2012– )

7.plot: Jamie and his family enjoy a picnic by the beach. The menu includes crispy chicken cutlets; stuffed summer squash boats; stone fruit cobbler; and grilled salad.

8.title: Playground Picnic

episode of.title: Home for Dinner with Jamie Deen (TV Series 2012– )

8.plot: Jamie uses honey in recipes to be served at a playground picnic. Included: baked sticky honey chicken; honey-glazed carrot-and-parsnip coins; olive oil-honey cake; and warm honey cider.

9.title: Bobby's Birthday

episode of.title: Home for Dinner with Jamie Deen (TV Series 2012– )

9.plot: Jamie cooks younger brother Bobby a birthday meal consisting of Bobby's favorite foods, including oven-roasted Brussels sprout salad with baby arugula; real Hungarian beef goulash; stout cake with caramel sauce.

10.title: Playdate Party

episode of.title: Home for Dinner with Jamie Deen (TV Series 2012– )

10.plot: Jamie prepares food for a play-date with friends. Included: guacamole deviled eggs; beer-can chicken; potato salad with green beans and pesto; watermelon skewers with sweet cloud dip.

11.title: Bag Lady Reunion

episode of.title: Home for Dinner with Jamie Deen (TV Series 2012– )

11.plot: Jamie celebrates the 25th anniversary of the Bag Lady catering service that he ran w/Paula & Bobby, who join him in the kitchen as they make egg-salad sandwiches, chicken salad, dill-pickle chips, and, for dessert, ooey-gooey butter cake.

12.title: Dads Just Wanna Have Fun!

episode of.title: Home for Dinner with Jamie Deen (TV Series 2012– )

12.plot: On the menu is corned beef with rutabagas and turnips; kale-and-potato casserole; soda bread; and a virgin mule.

13.title: Mom's Garden

episode of.title: Home for Dinner with Jamie Deen (TV Series 2012– )

13.plot: Jamie cooks a meal with produce he obtains from his mother's garden. He prepares rosemary pork chops with creamed corn and bacon, along with quick-braised collards and seasonal greens. For dessert, he makes a berry crisp with pistachios and oats.

1.title: Home for Dinner

episode of.title: Home for Dinner with Jamie Deen (TV Series 2012– )

1.plot: Jamie Deen prepares butterflied chicken with roasted root vegetables and pan gravy, a green salad with homemade dressing, and a lemon tart.

2.title: Burgers!

episode of.title: Home for Dinner with Jamie Deen (TV Series 2012– )

2.plot: Jamie makes one of his family's favorites: gazpacho, with lots of vegetables; the "Deen" burger; chocolate cake.

3.title: Taco Fiesta

episode of.title: Home for Dinner with Jamie Deen (TV Series 2012– )

3.plot: Skirt-steak tacos are served with salad roja, charred-corn salad and guacamole.

4.title: Breakfast Brunch

episode of.title: Home for Dinner with Jamie Deen (TV Series 2012– )

4.plot: The Deen family visit Ottawa Farms in Bloomingdale, Ga., to pick berries and gather ingredients for their Sunday brunch. On the menu: steel-cut oatmeal with banana and strawberries; hash-brown cakes; tropical fruit salad with honey & lime.

5.title: Dinner with Ginny

episode of.title: Home for Dinner with Jamie Deen (TV Series 2012– )

5.plot: Jamie's mom, Paula Deen, is coming over for dinner, so he prepares some of her favorite dishes, including grilled lemon-rosemary chicken; bow-tie pasta salad; and strawberries-and-cream ice cream.

6.title: Dad's Day Off

episode of.title: Home for Dinner with Jamie Deen (TV Series 2012– )

6.plot: Chili is made, along with cast-iron skillet bread, a crunchy chopped salad and salted-caramel-pecan pie.

7.title: Anniversary Dinner for Brooke

episode of.title: Home for Dinner with Jamie Deen (TV Series 2012– )

7.plot: Jamie prepares an elegant anniversary dinner for his wife, Brooke Deen. On the menu: rosemary beef tenderloin with blackberry-red-wine sauce; potatoes au gratin; shredded Brussels sprouts.

8.title: Backyard BBQ

episode of.title: Home for Dinner with Jamie Deen (TV Series 2012– )

8.plot: Baby-back ribs, twice-baked potatoes and chewy toffee treats are made for a backyard barbecue.

9.title: Jack's Favorite Things

episode of.title: Home for Dinner with Jamie Deen (TV Series 2012– )

9.plot: Jamie prepares some of son Jack's favorite foods, including chicken salad in toast cups; pimento-cheese dip; broccoli salad; purple smoothies.

10.title: Dinner for Two

episode of.title: Home for Dinner with Jamie Deen (TV Series 2012– )

10.plot: Jamie Deen prepares a quick and healthful dinner for his mother, Paula. On the menu: tilapia in foil packets; herbed couscous with golden raisins and pine nuts; green-bean salad.
